7 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
8 Section 1. Part IV of Chapter 3 of Title 51 of the Louisiana Revised Statutes of 1950,
9 comprised of R.S. 51:955.1 through 955.2, is hereby enacted to read as follows:
10 PART IV: LOUISIANA WOOD PELLET MANUFACTURING STRENGTHENING
11 ACT
12 §955.1. Findings; purpose
13 A. The legislature hereby finds and declares that the wood pellet
14 manufacturing industry represents a significant economic opportunity for the state,
15 leveraging the state's abundant forest resources, world-class deepwater port facilities,
16 and extensive rail network to serve growing international demand for renewable
17 biomass fuel. Wood pellet manufacturing creates high-quality jobs in rural
18 communities, supports the forestry sector, and diversifies the state's economy. The
19 legislature further finds that the current regulatory framework, while serving
20 important environmental and public safety purposes, was not designed with the
