5 B. It is the purpose of this Act to establish this state as a premier location for
6 wood pellet manufacturing by streamlining permitting processes while maintaining
7 appropriate environmental safeguards, developing a skilled workforce to meet the
8 industry's employment needs, and facilitating the efficient transportation and export
9 of wood pellets through this state's port facilities, thereby enabling the state to
10 capture a significant share of the growing international market, create jobs, support
11 rural communities, and strengthen this state's economy.
12 §955.2. Wood pellet manufacturing; definitions; priority industry; port access
13 A. As used in this Part, "wood pellet manufacturing" means the production
14 of compressed biomass pellets from forestry residues for export or domestic use,
15 including those supplying fuel markets driven by new and transformative sources of
16 power generation.
17 B. Louisiana Economic Development, in accordance with the Administrative
18 Procedure Act, shall establish wood pellet manufacturing as a priority industry in this
19 state, and shall promulgate rules and regulations including but not be limited to the
20 following:
21 (1) Prioritizing and enhancing job creation incentives for wood pellet
22 manufacturing facilities.
23 (2) Establishing workforce development and training initiatives for wood
24 pellet manufacturing facilities.
25 (3) Prioritizing wood pellet cargo for loading, docking, and processing at
26 state ports.
27 (4) Establishing site readiness criteria for wood pellet manufacturing.
28 (5) Providing clear regulatory pathways for the development of wood pellet
29 manufacturing facilities throughout this state.
