HB 670 Original 2026 Regular Session Owen
Abstract: Directs Louisiana Economic Development to designate wood pellet
manufacturing as a priority industry in this state, and to promulgate rules and
regulations to spur industry development.
Proposed law provides for legislative findings and intent.
Proposed law defines "wood pellet manufacturing".
Proposed law directs Louisiana Economic Development to establish wood pellet
manufacturing as a priority industry in this state, and to promulgate rules and regulations
including but not limited to the following:
(1) Prioritizing and enhancing job creation incentives for wood pellet manufacturing
facilities.
(2) Establishing workforce development and training initiatives for wood pellet
manufacturing facilities.
(3) Prioritizing wood pellet cargo for loading, docking, and processing at state ports.
(4) Establishing site readiness criteria for wood pellet manufacturing.
(5) Providing clear regulatory pathways for the development of wood pellet
manufacturing facilities throughout this state.
